title: Grateful Dead Live at Saenger Performing Arts Center on 1980-10-19
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi 1000-II > Sound Devices USB Pre-2 > WAV 2496. Edits: WAV 2496 > Wavelab > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Concert recording & transfer by Richie Stankiewicz, edits by Andrew F. 09/2013.
description:
Set 1

On The Road Again, Jack A Roe, Dark Hollow, Rosalie McFall, Cassidy, Bird Song, Heaven Help The Fool, Ain't No Lie-> Ripple

Set 2

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried, Mexicali Blues, Candyman, Passenger, Row Jimmy-> Looks Like Rain-> Tennessee Jed-> Promised Land

Set 3

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia-> Good Lovin', E: Brokedown Palace

First Set Acoustic

reviews.review_text: candidate for a best ever aud This is quite close to the top of the list of Grateful Dead AUDS. Liten to Candyman if you need 'proof'.  Amazing clarity, stereo and vocals.  Richie Stankiewicz was quite a taper- a bLLesing he is sharing with us aLL. - jamie w.

I agree with below This recording is very very good. Considering they popped into town for only 2 shows in the middle of this historic run of shows. The band is on and recording is just as good as the boys energy. 
 You did a great job pulling off this one.
Thank you Been wanting a good clean sounding version of this show for years. A beauty from start to finish.
Thank you! My favorite Tennessee Jed ever. As it was mentioned before, it's awesome to have a complete AUD from this show where the taper doesn't talk the whole time.
Great field recording, but It sounds like some sort of digital noise reduction was applied in the "mastering" phase. Love to hear the raw recording.

New Orleans Or Bust...ed  Grate Taping Job Under Hostile Conditions. You'd Think The Dead Would Be A Li'l Easier On Busting People In New Orleans. I Was Told They Were Hauling 'em Out By The Handfuls. Mr. Stankiewicz And Beyer As Usual Bring Home The Bacon, And This One Sizzles With Low Heat. So It Comes Out Just So. May The Goddess Bless The Tapers As They Have Blessed Us. Thanks, For Always Grateful.
